{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/TangentCone/Seq.html#mem_tangentConeAt_iff_exists_seq_norm_tendsto_atTop\"><span class=\"name\">mem_tangentConeAt_iff_exists_seq_norm_tendsto_atTop</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Field/Basic.html#NontriviallyNormedField\">NontriviallyNormedField</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#NormedAddCommGroup\">NormedAddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/Basic.html#NormedSpace\">NormedSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">s</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#Set\">Set</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">x </span><span class=\"fn\">y</span> : <span class=\"fn\">E</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">y</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Membership.mem\">∈</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/TangentCone/Defs.html#tangentConeAt\">tangentConeAt</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">s</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Iff\">↔</a>   <span class=\"fn\">∃ (<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a> → <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span></span>) (<span class=\"fn\">d</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a> → <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>),\n    <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Tendsto\">Filter.Tendsto</a> <span class=\"fn\">(fun (<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>) =&gt; <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">c</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a>)</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/AtTopBot/Defs.html#Filter.atTop\">Filter.atTop</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/AtTopBot/Defs.html#Filter.atTop\">Filter.atTop</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a>       <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Eventually\">∀ᶠ</a> (<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>) <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Eventually\">in</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/AtTopBot/Defs.html#Filter.atTop\">Filter.atTop</a><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Eventually\">,</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAdd.hAdd\">+</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">d</span> <span class=\"fn\">n</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Membership.mem\">∈</a> <span class=\"fn\">s</span>)</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Tendsto\">Filter.Tendsto</a> <span class=\"fn\">(fun (<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">c</span> <span class=\"fn\">n</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSMul.hSMul\">•</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">d</span> <span class=\"fn\">n</span></span>)</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/AtTopBot/Defs.html#Filter.atTop\">Filter.atTop</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Filter.html#nhds\">nhds</a> <span class=\"fn\">y</span>)</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"In a normed space over a nontrivially normed field,\na point `y` belongs to the tangent cone of a set `s` at `x`\niff there exiss a sequence of scalars `c n` and a sequence of points `d n` such that\n\n- `‖c n‖ → ∞` as `n → ∞`;\n- `x + d n ∈ s` for sufficiently large `n`;\n- `c n • d n` tendst to `y`.\n\nBefore https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/34127,\nthe right-hand side of this equivalence was the definition of the tangent cone.\n\nIn most cases, `exists_fun_of_mem_tangentConeAt` and/or `mem_tangentConeAt_of_seq`\ncan be used to generalize a proof using this lemma to topological vector spaces.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/TangentCone/Seq.html#mem_tangentConeAt_iff_exists_seq_norm_tendsto_atTop","kind":"theorem","line":75,"name":"mem_tangentConeAt_iff_exists_seq_norm_tendsto_atTop","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/TangentCone/Seq.lean#L75-L132"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/TangentCone/Seq.html#mem_tangentConeAt_of_pow_smul\"><span class=\"name\">mem_tangentConeAt_of_pow_smul</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Field/Basic.html#NormedDivisionRing\">NormedDivisionRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#AddCommGroup\">AddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/Defs.html#Module\">Module</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Basic.html#TopologicalSpace\">TopologicalSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/MulAction.html#ContinuousSMul\">ContinuousSMul</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">s</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#Set\">Set</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">x </span><span class=\"fn\">y</span> : <span class=\"fn\">E</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">r</span> : <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hr₀</span> : <span class=\"fn\">r</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Ne\">≠</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hr</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\">r</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hs</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Eventually\">∀ᶠ</a> (<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>) <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Eventually\">in</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/AtTopBot/Defs.html#Filter.atTop\">Filter.atTop</a><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Eventually\">,</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAdd.hAdd\">+</a> <span class=\"fn\">r</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> <span class=\"fn\">n</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSMul.hSMul\">•</a> <span class=\"fn\">y</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Membership.mem\">∈</a> <span class=\"fn\">s</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">y</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Membership.mem\">∈</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/TangentCone/Defs.html#tangentConeAt\">tangentConeAt</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">s</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/TangentCone/Seq.html#mem_tangentConeAt_of_pow_smul","kind":"theorem","line":66,"name":"mem_tangentConeAt_of_pow_smul","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/TangentCone/Seq.lean#L66-L71"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/TangentCone/Seq.html#tangentConeAt.lim_zero\"><span class=\"name\">tangentConeAt</span>.<span class=\"name\">lim_zero</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Field/Basic.html#NormedDivisionRing\">NormedDivisionRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#AddCommGroup\">AddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/Defs.html#Module\">Module</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Basic.html#TopologicalSpace\">TopologicalSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/MulAction.html#ContinuousSMul\">ContinuousSMul</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_3}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">l</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter\">Filter</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">d</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">y</span> : <span class=\"fn\">E</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hc</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Tendsto\">Filter.Tendsto</a> <span class=\"fn\">(fun (<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <span class=\"fn\">α</span>) =&gt; <a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">c</span> <span class=\"fn\">n</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">l</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/AtTopBot/Defs.html#Filter.atTop\">Filter.atTop</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hd</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Tendsto\">Filter.Tendsto</a> <span class=\"fn\">(fun (<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <span class=\"fn\">α</span>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">c</span> <span class=\"fn\">n</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSMul.hSMul\">•</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">d</span> <span class=\"fn\">n</span></span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">l</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Filter.html#nhds\">nhds</a> <span class=\"fn\">y</span>)</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Tendsto\">Filter.Tendsto</a> <span class=\"fn\">d</span> <span class=\"fn\">l</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Filter.html#nhds\">nhds</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Auxiliary lemma ensuring that, under the assumptions from an old definition of the tangent cone,\nthe sequence `d` tends to 0 at infinity. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/TangentCone/Seq.html#tangentConeAt.lim_zero","kind":"theorem","line":56,"name":"tangentConeAt.lim_zero","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/TangentCone/Seq.lean#L56-L64"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/TangentCone/Seq.html#mem_tangentConeAt_iff_exists_seq\"><span class=\"name\">mem_tangentConeAt_iff_exists_seq</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">R</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#AddCommGroup\">AddCommGroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#SMul\">SMul</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Basic.html#TopologicalSpace\">TopologicalSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Bases.html#FirstCountableTopology\">FirstCountableTopology</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">s</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#Set\">Set</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">x </span><span class=\"fn\">y</span> : <span class=\"fn\">E</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">y</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Membership.mem\">∈</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/TangentCone/Defs.html#tangentConeAt\">tangentConeAt</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span> <span class=\"fn\">s</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Iff\">↔</a>   <span class=\"fn\">∃ (<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a> → <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span>) (<span class=\"fn\">d</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a> → <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>),\n    <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Tendsto\">Filter.Tendsto</a> <span class=\"fn\">d</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/AtTopBot/Defs.html#Filter.atTop\">Filter.atTop</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Filter.html#nhds\">nhds</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a>       <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Eventually\">∀ᶠ</a> (<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>) <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Eventually\">in</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/AtTopBot/Defs.html#Filter.atTop\">Filter.atTop</a><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Eventually\">,</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAdd.hAdd\">+</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">d</span> <span class=\"fn\">n</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Membership.mem\">∈</a> <span class=\"fn\">s</span>)</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Tendsto\">Filter.Tendsto</a> <span class=\"fn\">(fun (<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">ℕ</a>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">c</span> <span class=\"fn\">n</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSMul.hSMul\">•</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">d</span> <span class=\"fn\">n</span></span>)</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/AtTopBot/Defs.html#Filter.atTop\">Filter.atTop</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Filter.html#nhds\">nhds</a> <span class=\"fn\">y</span>)</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"In a vector space with first countable topology, a vector `y` belongs to `tangentConeAt 𝕜 s x`\nif and only if there exist sequences `c n` and `d n` such that\n\n- `d n` tends to zero as `n → ∞`;\n- `x + d n ∈ s` for sufficiently large `n`;\n- `c n • d n` tends to `y` as `n → ∞`.\n\nSee `mem_tangentConeAt_of_seq` and `exists_fun_of_mem_tangentConeAt`\nfor versions of two implications of this theorem that don't assume first countable topology. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/TangentCone/Seq.html#mem_tangentConeAt_iff_exists_seq","kind":"theorem","line":29,"name":"mem_tangentConeAt_iff_exists_seq","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/Calculus/TangentCone/Seq.lean#L29-L50"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Analysis.Calculus.TangentCone.Basic","Mathlib.Topology.Algebra.MulAction","Mathlib.Analysis.Normed.Module.Basic","Mathlib.Analysis.SpecificLimits.Normed"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.Analysis.Calculus.TangentCone.Seq"}